// Config.xcconfig.example
//
// Local build settings for the Glide Xcode project. These are kept out of
// project.pbxproj (and out of git) because they are per-developer: your own
// Clerk application, your own Apple Developer Team, optionally your own
// local server URL.
//
// Setup:
//   1. cp Config.xcconfig.example Config.xcconfig
//   2. Fill in the values below.
//   3. Open Glide.xcodeproj — the Glide target's Debug and Release build
//      configurations already reference Config.xcconfig as their base
//      configuration, so Xcode picks these up automatically.
//
// Config.xcconfig is gitignored. Without it, the Glide target's
// baseConfigurationReference points at a file that does not exist, so the
// build fails immediately instead of silently signing with, or
// authenticating against, someone else's credentials.

// Required. The Clerk publishable key for the Clerk application your
// server (apps/server, CLERK_SECRET_KEY) is configured with. Must be the
// publishable key from the SAME Clerk app, or every request will 401.
// Find it in the Clerk dashboard under API Keys. Injected into
// Glide/Info.plist as ClerkPublishableKey and read by
// AppBundleConfiguration.clerkPublishableKey.
CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY = pk_test_YOUR_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY_HERE

// Required. Your Apple Developer Team ID, used for code signing
// (Signing & Capabilities > Team). Find it at
// https://developer.apple.com/account under Membership, or in Xcode's
// account settings. A free personal team works for local development.
DEVELOPMENT_TEAM = YOUR_TEAM_ID_HERE

// Optional. Overrides the Worker base URL the app talks to. Only needed if
// you are not running the Worker at the default http://localhost:8787
// (e.g. pnpm run dev:server on a different port, or a deployed Worker).
// Read by AppBundleConfiguration.serverBaseURL via Info.plist's
// GlideServerBaseURL key; falls back to http://localhost:8787 if unset.
// GLIDE_SERVER_BASE_URL = http://localhost:8787

// Optional. The project.pbxproj Build Settings for the Glide target already
// set these to sane, non-secret defaults (glide / glide://callback) — they
// are not credentials, so they are not required here. Uncomment only if you
// need a different URL scheme, and note the matching line still hardcoded
// in project.pbxproj's target Build Settings will take precedence unless
// you also remove it there.
// CLERK_CALLBACK_SCHEME = glide
// CLERK_REDIRECT_URL = glide://callback
